In the One Hundred and Ninety-Fourth General Court
(2025-2026)
_______________
An Act relative to changing the two-year elected term for the Mayor of Chicopee to a four-year
elected term.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. At the next annual municipal election in the City of Chicopee, and at such
2 election in every fourth year thereafter, the mayor shall be elected by the qualified voters of the
3 City voting in their respective precincts. The mayor shall be elected by ballot and shall hold
4 office for four years from the first Monday in January following the election at which they were
5 elected, and until a successor is elected and qualified.
6 SECTION 2. Chapter 144 of the acts of 1917 is hereby repealed.
7 SECTION 3. So much of the charter of said City and of the amendments thereto as is
8 inconsistent herewith is hereby repealed.
9 SECTION 4. This act shall take effect upon its acceptance by a majority of the qualified
10 voters of the City of Chicopee, present and voting therein at the state election in the current year.
